>> good morning, thank you, Madam chair, I usually try to speak directly to the items on the agenda but I am so overwhelmed with what's going on this morning at the Alameda County board of supervisors meeting that started at 9:30 and how it relates to you as a body, so on that agenda, they have the Homekey shelter operation getting 1.7 million dollars, St. Mary's center housing getting 195 thousand dollars, Centro de la Raza raising the emergency rental assistance program from 11.1 million dollars to 24.8 million dollars, and another item on the agenda Whee Centro de la Raza will be getting 4.1 million dollars for rental assistance programs.

East Bay Asian youth center getting 91 thousand 910 thousand dollars, the Lao family will be sharing with 7 other Non-Profits 8.2 million dollars, and I remember vividly that Councilmember Larry Reid was strongly objecting to Centro de la Raza having the ability to distribute money related to housing and rental assistance and legal assistance around housing Eviction because they had no relationship with the African American community.

He gave them an opportunity to do outreach and after a period of time, he identified that they were unable to do it, but the biggest thing is we have money that's going to Non-Profits that's coming from outside sources and that money is not being weighed in on by you as a body to determine equity, fairness and other issues, at the same time, African Americans are not being served well even with Alameda County.
Thank you.
